# NOLidarWireframeContour — Project Memory

## Active focus

ACT Phase 2 standalone: Lidar Wireframe Contour (NOLoader mod).

## Architecture

- **Probe:** `LidarSphereCastProbe` — Cast#1/Cast#2 origin offset; `TerrainLayerMask=2112`; min hit 12m
- Probe: 5 Hz default, 20 Hz near TTI; per-frame extrapolation + smoothed uniforms (P39)
- **GPU:** `LidarDepthCapturePass` (R32 depth + half-res edge @60Hz) + `LidarWireframeRenderPass` (backbuffer FullScreenPass)
- **Uniforms:** probe on CPU; fade/boot via shader `_CombatStartTime`/`_CombatEndTime` + `_Time.y`
- **VRAM:** `Cleanup()` on Shutdown / gpu gate off / controller OnDestroy
- **Depth:** `requiresDepthTexture` while gpu gate OR `ForceKeepDepthTextureActive` (default false)
- **Patches:** `FlightHud::Awake`, `FlightHud::SetAircraft` + `EnsureController()` fallback

## Deploy

`.\scripts\deploy-mod.ps1` → `Nuclear Option\NOLoader\mods\LidarWireframeContour\`

## Version

0.2.6V — render-rate cone smooth; 1s escape hold; static CRT (no noise flicker).

Legacy DEV channel (P28–P40) retired; see CHANGELOG `[0.1.0]`.

## Project specifics

- Runtime requires `NOLoader.LidarWireframeContour.dll` + `NOLidarWireframeContour_Data/lidar_shaders` (loose Shaders/ NOT used; hash in `shader_source_hash.txt`)
- build-shader-bundle.ps1 syncs Data/Shaders → UnityBundleBuilder before Unity build
- Composite: backbuffer fullscreen (FullScreenPass pattern), not swap-blip only
- Edge: Laplacian + hard NMS + flat-kill + `EdgeTexelScale` (P38 razor lines)
- Mode 0 combat: velocity cone + CRT + boot strobe (`AppearBootSec`) + `HudBrightness`
- No `ImpactDepthMask` in mode 0 (probe jitter caused horizontal bands)
- Mode 3 = terrain edge debug without HUD effects

